description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic clinical support worker to support the radiology service at Westmorland General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be full time at 37.5 hours per week. Days and hours to be decided but will include working some 12.5 hour days and rotational weekend and Bank Holiday work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will mainly be supporting the radiographers in clinical duties in X-ray, CT, MRI, screening, and ultrasound, and will include supporting in sterile procedures and venepuncture. You will also be involved in the smooth and efficient running of these services including some admin and clerical duties, for example making appointments on the computerised Radiology Information System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will be expected to be well organised, have an interest in patient care, good communication skills and familiarity with IT systems. Ideally you will have experience of relevant work in a healthcare environment and have a level 3 NVQ or equivalent in healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the Trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period. This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJoanne ParkJob titleDeputy Head X-Ray FGHEmail addressjoanne.park@mbht.nhs.ukTelephone number01229 51033Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
